dxf2svg.svg
Class SvgObject

java.lang.Object
  dxf2svg.svg.SvgElement
      dxf2svg.svg.SvgObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
Direct Known Subclasses:
SvgGraphicElement, SvgObjectX, SvgText
public class SvgObject
extends SvgElement

This class encapsulates the basic SVG object.

While SvgObject is the base class for all other Svg objects it can also be instantiated as an object of 'unknown' type. This allows new or undefined Acad objects to be written to the SVG file providing a sort of debug feature. The object appears as a text string of the name of the object at the location it would have appeared in the DXF, but only if DEBUG is set. If it is not set you get a warning on the command line about an un handled object.

Version:
2.10 - May 13, 2003
Author:
Andrew Nisbet

setFill

protected void setFill(java.lang.String fill)
Set an object's fill as a 6 digit hex String preceeded by a '#'. Called by sub-class objects that can take a fill in SVG but don't in DXF (circle, path, ellipse). If the argument String in empty then this method assumes that the object does not take a fill attribute and resets the value of Fill to null.

Parameters:
fill - String value of fill (a colour like blue or #0066ff).

setFill

public void setFill(int AcadColourNumber)
Translates a integer argument into a hex String preceeded by a # and sets an object's fill to that colour value. If the argument value is zero (0) the colour is not set;

AcadColourNumber - Colour as integer.

This allows new or undefined Acad objects to be written to the SVG file providing a sort of debug feature. The object appears as a text string of the name of the object at the location it would have appeared in the DXF, but only id DEBUG is set.
